WEBVTT

00:30.541 --> 00:32.875
Many people call us idols,

00:33.625 --> 00:37.083
heroines, icons,
stars, leaders,

00:37.416 --> 00:38.500
and they are right.

00:38.916 --> 00:41.625
But we do our work very humbly.

00:43.333 --> 00:44.541
A poet said:

00:45.666 --> 00:48.583
With great powers
come great responsibilities.

00:49.000 --> 00:54.125
And yes, we have used
the power of the SOS MAMIS

00:54.750 --> 00:57.833
for the good of the Saint
Michael School community,

00:58.208 --> 01:00.958
each of us, however,
is very different,

01:01.125 --> 01:03.708
but our strength
comes from our unity.

01:04.583 --> 01:06.041
Milagros,

01:06.458 --> 01:08.708
with her mountain-moving faith.

01:10.625 --> 01:11.625
Luna,

01:11.791 --> 01:14.625
our Captain Planet,
who always brings us

01:14.708 --> 01:16.625
-closer to Earth.
-Pacha Mama.

01:16.833 --> 01:17.875
That too.

01:17.958 --> 01:21.041
Julia.
Julia, our CEO.

01:21.208 --> 01:23.166
Who has taught each one of us

01:23.250 --> 01:25.458
that we can be
the Big Boss of our lives.

01:26.375 --> 01:27.541
And Clarita,

01:28.166 --> 01:30.375
our Clarita,
with her tools...

01:30.916 --> 01:31.958
Sorry, sorry, sorry.

01:32.083 --> 01:33.666
The screen, Clarita!

01:33.750 --> 01:35.166
Just a second.

01:36.291 --> 01:39.625
I was pretty sure,
that I had left it secured.

01:40.041 --> 01:41.375
This happens every day.

01:41.958 --> 01:44.625
I'll have to put a stone
with a wire to hold it

01:44.708 --> 01:46.125
because the springs are bad.

01:46.208 --> 01:47.250
-So...
-Hurry up.

01:47.333 --> 01:48.500
I pull it down,
but the springs....

01:48.583 --> 01:51.375
I think everyone
understood very clearly

01:51.458 --> 01:53.291
the contribution you have made
to the school community.

01:53.375 --> 01:54.500
Relax, Regina, I'm not done.

01:54.625 --> 01:56.083
There are other more pressing matters.

01:56.166 --> 01:59.416
You' ve been there for more
than 20 minutes, what is left to say?

01:59.958 --> 02:02.125
-Trini, me!
-Sure, Luna!

02:02.416 --> 02:04.125
Solve it fast.
Let's not waste any more time,

02:04.208 --> 02:05.791
mine costs money, okay? Bye.

02:12.750 --> 02:16.208
Please stop speaking
in that native language.

02:16.291 --> 02:17.375
Ok? Please.

02:19.458 --> 02:21.416
Father, Anthony, please come with me.

02:21.500 --> 02:23.750
-As vice president...
-Treasurer.

02:23.875 --> 02:26.125
-Is the same.
-Is not the same.

02:26.208 --> 02:28.375
I am honored to introduce

02:28.458 --> 02:31.375
the first family to benefit

02:31.458 --> 02:34.166
from the Clarita
Arts and Sciences grant,

02:34.250 --> 02:36.708
with a self-sacrificing mother
who has managed

02:36.833 --> 02:39.625
to raise her son on her own.

02:39.708 --> 02:42.875
With Father Anthony
we entrust ourselves to the Lord

02:42.958 --> 02:45.375
to make the best decision.

02:45.833 --> 02:47.291
And we did.

02:47.416 --> 02:50.375
Yes, with Milagros
we are a very good couple.

02:50.750 --> 02:52.166
Right, Milagros?

02:52.958 --> 02:54.916
Team, Father. Team.

02:55.166 --> 02:57.125
And we worked many nights.

02:57.291 --> 02:58.250
Luna!

02:58.333 --> 02:59.500
So many.

02:59.958 --> 03:02.750
In a spiritual retreat in Pomaire.

03:02.833 --> 03:04.708
What happened in Pomaire,
stays in Pomaire.

03:04.791 --> 03:06.250
Nights with a lot of passion.

03:06.375 --> 03:09.208
Like the passion of Jesus,
with sacrifice, with pain.

03:09.291 --> 03:11.833
And it is a process
that has brought me much pleasure.

03:11.916 --> 03:13.250
With Milagros, of course.

03:13.333 --> 03:14.416
Well done, Millie.

03:14.541 --> 03:16.041
Well, I want to introduce you

03:16.125 --> 03:19.083
to Álex Quintanilla and his mother,

03:19.791 --> 03:20.833
Daniela Muñoz.

03:22.125 --> 03:24.375
Bravo, our grant student.

03:24.583 --> 03:25.833
Bravo, bravo!

03:28.166 --> 03:30.166
Thank you very much to all.

03:31.916 --> 03:33.833
I wanted to thank you for

03:34.583 --> 03:36.791
welcoming us in this beautiful community,

03:37.458 --> 03:40.583
with my Alex we have not had
a very good time

03:40.666 --> 03:43.291
-due to the death of his father, but...
-Such a pity!

03:43.375 --> 03:46.833
...we knew that we would find
kind hearts in this capital.

03:47.916 --> 03:50.583
Well, Daniela comes from Mechuque,

03:50.666 --> 03:52.958
a very colorful island in Chiloé.

03:53.541 --> 03:54.666
Yes.

03:54.750 --> 03:57.625
Thank you all very much...
To Milagros and Father Anthony.

03:57.875 --> 03:58.875
Thanks.

03:58.958 --> 04:01.333
I only have one doubt.
I was checking the grant,

04:01.416 --> 04:04.583
what it includes, and I wanted to know
if it includes the school supplies,

04:04.666 --> 04:06.875
because I sent several emails
and I have not heard back.

04:06.958 --> 04:09.083
Thank you very much, Daniela, really.

04:09.166 --> 04:13.083
I am sure that Alex will have
a nice time at our school.

04:13.458 --> 04:16.333
Well, I guess you're not
the kind of people

04:16.416 --> 04:18.375
who want everything for free,
are you?

04:18.541 --> 04:20.083
-No? Ah, good.
-No...

04:20.166 --> 04:22.083
All right, seat.

04:22.166 --> 04:24.291
-Maria Grace, please.
-Did she hit you?

04:24.666 --> 04:26.291
I would like to remind everyone

04:26.375 --> 04:29.000
that this month we have
a mandatory charity event

04:29.083 --> 04:31.791
to raise funds for the nursing home
"Grandpa, tell me"

04:31.875 --> 04:34.500
one of the many humanitarian causes
that my foundation is in charge of.

04:34.583 --> 04:38.125
So, the collaboration
of all parents is very important.

04:38.208 --> 04:38.958
Each and all.

04:39.041 --> 04:41.291
Each and all parents

04:42.166 --> 04:43.416
without any exception.

04:47.041 --> 04:48.208
Don't worry.

04:57.708 --> 05:01.166
The supplies are not included
in the grant. Outrageous.

05:01.250 --> 05:02.958
ALERT!
PROTOCOL

05:03.166 --> 05:06.041
Neither are the school uniforms.
It's in the fine print of the grant

05:06.125 --> 05:07.625
which is not so fine.

05:07.708 --> 05:10.791
Well, we did everything
with the best of intentions.

05:10.875 --> 05:13.041
This world is full
of good intentions.

05:13.125 --> 05:14.333
That is corruption.

05:14.416 --> 05:15.541
We all know that the principal

05:15.625 --> 05:18.000
is in collusion with the guy
who sells the uniforms.

05:18.083 --> 05:21.000
-They are lovers.
-No, it's a rumour.

05:21.625 --> 05:22.791
Who has a tumor?

05:22.916 --> 05:24.208
I AM OUTRAGEED

05:25.041 --> 05:26.791
Our grant holder is very beautiful.

05:26.958 --> 05:29.166
Beautiful?
I find her quite normal.

05:29.791 --> 05:32.541
I was going through the spreadsheet
and we have a little money.

05:32.625 --> 05:35.541
We could give her
all the school supplies for the year.

05:35.750 --> 05:37.041
Like a welcome gift.

05:37.125 --> 05:40.458
No, the poor should not be given
fried fish on a platter.

05:40.541 --> 05:42.291
You have to teach them to fish.

05:42.583 --> 05:45.500
What if we invite her to our rehearsal
and give her the gift there?

05:51.916 --> 05:53.041
Will it be fine?

05:53.166 --> 05:55.875
We've been rehearsing for weeks,
mishap included.

05:55.958 --> 05:57.791
Obviously she won't be able to.
It is for advanced.

05:57.958 --> 06:01.041
Come on. I missed two weeks
due to my trip to France.

06:01.125 --> 06:03.541
I closed three million-dollar contracts
and I know it by heart.

06:03.625 --> 06:06.791
I haven't missed any rehearsal
and I still haven't learned it!

06:06.958 --> 06:08.708
Puppy,
put the xylophone in the backpack!

06:08.875 --> 06:12.083
Well, let it be clear
that I don't agree with the song.

06:12.208 --> 06:13.208
WHAT?

06:13.291 --> 06:14.333
STOP IT...

06:14.708 --> 06:15.708
ENOUGH!

06:16.416 --> 06:18.541
No, I will not get tired of repeating it.

06:18.625 --> 06:21.125
Does anyone have a spare flute
for Blanquita?

06:21.291 --> 06:22.666
Gross.

06:23.250 --> 06:25.250
Juan de Dios,
don't forget the flute.

06:25.333 --> 06:27.625
Stretch!
Shoulder, neck, shoulder.

06:27.708 --> 06:30.750
For God's sake, my Pig.
He is so patient with boys.

06:30.833 --> 06:33.541
-Children
-Oh, yeah. Children.

06:35.375 --> 06:38.166
Hey, this little new child...

06:38.958 --> 06:41.541
It is very late. Why don't we just
start the rehearsal without her?

06:41.625 --> 06:42.916
Here comes, poor thing.

06:43.750 --> 06:46.833
All humble, so she won't feel bad
for not being an expert dancer like me.

06:46.916 --> 06:48.541
You are not an expert dancer.

06:48.625 --> 06:50.291
That's the attitude!

06:50.375 --> 06:52.041
-Hello!
-Hello, Piggy!

06:52.333 --> 06:53.625
Welcome, welcome!

06:53.708 --> 06:55.750
-Didn't you bring your sports outfit?
-No...

06:55.958 --> 06:58.333
Honey, look, go play with
the other children, they are kind.

06:58.416 --> 06:59.958
Pig! Love!

07:00.083 --> 07:02.083
Pig! It's the grant boy.

07:02.708 --> 07:03.708
What?

07:03.791 --> 07:05.916
Integrate him.
Make him play.

07:06.958 --> 07:09.250
No, Pig, my love!
Welcome the new child!

07:09.791 --> 07:10.833
It's okay.

07:11.375 --> 07:13.583
My Pig.
Oh, how cute your ginger!

07:13.666 --> 07:14.333
Right?

07:14.458 --> 07:15.291
-Hello.
-Hi, sir.

07:15.375 --> 07:16.958
Sofia, my love, come on.

07:17.041 --> 07:18.291
They say they bring good luck too.

07:18.375 --> 07:19.416
Make him play.

07:19.500 --> 07:22.291
Don't worry, because while we rehearse
my Pig will take care of them.

07:22.375 --> 07:24.583
He is the most feminist thing there is,
he always helps me with the puppies.

07:25.666 --> 07:27.708
And by God,
what a handsome man too.

07:29.083 --> 07:30.458
Okay. Come here

07:30.541 --> 07:33.250
and see us rehearse, because
she didn't bring her sporting outfit.

07:33.541 --> 07:35.208
-No, I did.
-But, you didn't tell me.

07:35.291 --> 07:37.541
Because you didn't let me.
What happened is that I came by bus,

07:37.625 --> 07:39.250
so I put my clothes under.

07:39.333 --> 07:41.041
Do you mind
if I take off my clothes here?

07:41.291 --> 07:43.416
-We are all free here.
-No! I do not!

07:43.583 --> 07:45.041
-I do not care.
-Me too.

07:45.125 --> 07:46.583
So I do not slow you down.

07:47.958 --> 07:48.750
Okey, okey.

07:48.833 --> 07:50.875
Well, don't worry about learning
all the choreography today,

07:50.958 --> 07:52.958
because the presentation
is actually in another month.

07:53.250 --> 07:54.291
Ready.

07:54.541 --> 07:57.125
How beautiful, the most folkloric there
is, I love it, it's very Chilean.

07:57.208 --> 07:58.958
And come on Macarena and...

07:59.041 --> 08:01.708
Shinning, and shinning and shinning.

08:01.791 --> 08:03.750
Then swimming!
And swimming

08:04.000 --> 08:05.916
and swimming.
Travolta!

08:06.208 --> 08:08.375
Travolta... Stop, stop.

08:08.500 --> 08:10.875
Trinity, Travolta is like groove,

08:10.958 --> 08:12.291
Right? Travolta...

08:12.375 --> 08:15.083
-Okay.
-Good. Ok, from Travolta, everybody.

08:15.208 --> 08:16.208
All together.

08:16.291 --> 08:19.041
Travolta, Travolta, Travolta.

08:19.416 --> 08:21.708
Rib, rib, rib.

08:21.791 --> 08:22.958
And now...

08:23.125 --> 08:25.125
Sunrise, sunrise. Stop.

08:25.708 --> 08:27.541
Trini. Sunrise!

08:28.166 --> 08:30.291
-Okay.
-Five, six, seven, eight.

08:30.500 --> 08:32.582
Sunrise!

08:32.666 --> 08:34.832
And one, two, three, four.

08:35.041 --> 08:37.041
Kick and up!

08:37.332 --> 08:39.041
-What now!
-Let's stop a little,

08:39.125 --> 08:41.041
-I pulled a muscle.
-Everybody, take five.

08:41.125 --> 08:42.625
-Material fatigue.
-Daniela, please come here.

08:43.957 --> 08:45.666
-Go.
-Yeah, relax.

08:46.416 --> 08:48.041
Daniela, I'm impressed!

08:48.125 --> 08:50.625
-Thank you!
-I want everyone to follow Daniela.

08:50.708 --> 08:53.500
Daniela has the groove
this dance needs

08:53.583 --> 08:55.541
and we hadn't achieved in a month.

08:55.625 --> 08:57.541
Daniela, please take Trini's position.

08:57.625 --> 08:58.791
Trini go to the back.

08:58.875 --> 09:01.041
Wait, sorry,
if we don't respect the formation

09:01.125 --> 09:03.833
everyone else will get confused
without having me as a reference.

09:03.916 --> 09:05.541
Girls, is anyone confused?

09:05.625 --> 09:06.625
-No.
-No.

09:06.708 --> 09:08.541
-Great!
-Daniela, please.

09:08.625 --> 09:09.666
Excuse me, Trini.

09:09.750 --> 09:11.333
Trinity, to the back.

09:11.625 --> 09:13.166
-Let's go.
-From the beginning?

09:13.500 --> 09:14.875
From the top.

09:17.625 --> 09:18.875
Oops, we are together!

09:18.958 --> 09:20.208
Five, six, seven, eight.

09:20.333 --> 09:24.666
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

09:24.750 --> 09:26.541
Chuchuka, chuchuka.

09:26.625 --> 09:28.750
And Macarena to the side, yes!

09:29.333 --> 09:30.458
Let's see...

09:31.541 --> 09:33.708
Warm, warm, warm, warm.

09:35.250 --> 09:36.708
How nice, Daniela.

09:37.416 --> 09:41.041
Really integrated into the community,
a member of the group.

09:41.500 --> 09:43.500
She even gets along with your husband.

09:43.583 --> 09:45.916
I didn't know he was such
a great talker. Impressed.

09:46.000 --> 09:47.958
Look at my Inti playing with Alex.

09:48.041 --> 09:50.541
Good, even though my Dante
is very selective.

09:50.625 --> 09:54.125
You can tell this poor kid
was raised with good soft skills.

09:54.250 --> 09:56.583
Yes, my Sofi is also
the most soft skilled there is.

09:57.000 --> 09:59.541
Hey, it's getting late. Where is Milagros?
We must hand over the box.

09:59.625 --> 10:01.708
-Here I am, here I am.
-Finally, Millie!

10:01.833 --> 10:03.125
Well, quick,
it's too late now.

10:03.208 --> 10:04.625
Very late.
I have many things to do.

10:04.791 --> 10:05.500
Daniela!

10:05.583 --> 10:07.833
-Daniela.
-Got to go.

10:08.083 --> 10:09.625
Quick, pretty.

10:09.708 --> 10:11.333
-Come, sweetie.
-Yes, yes!

10:12.958 --> 10:14.458
Dear Daniela,

10:14.625 --> 10:15.833
on behalf of all...

10:15.916 --> 10:17.708
As president of the parents
of the 5th D,

10:17.791 --> 10:20.500
representing the SOS MAMIS,

10:20.708 --> 10:22.541
I would like to give you
this humble gift.

10:22.625 --> 10:25.041
We would like.

10:25.125 --> 10:26.125
Yes, we.

10:27.500 --> 10:29.208
-Here.
-For me?

10:29.291 --> 10:31.791
-What is this?
-The supplies for the whole year!

10:31.958 --> 10:34.125
-Yay!
-Bravo Bravo!

10:34.250 --> 10:37.666
Thank you very much, really,
I can't thank you enough...

10:37.750 --> 10:40.791
Whatever, make this quick,
I have to work. I work.

10:40.875 --> 10:42.875
Yes, actually,
I can't thank you enough...

10:42.958 --> 10:45.291
Great, great. Better that way,
let's go. Congratulations.

10:45.375 --> 10:46.541
-Thank you.
-Very good, sweetie.

10:46.625 --> 10:49.041
Honestly, I've never had this before.

10:49.541 --> 10:51.375
-Supplies?
-No.

10:52.958 --> 10:55.208
-Friends.
-Ugh, what a drag...

10:55.458 --> 10:56.458
Poor dear.

10:56.541 --> 10:57.625
So sweet.

10:59.875 --> 11:01.666
Oh, may the Lord protect her.

11:02.958 --> 11:04.416
We did it well.

11:08.041 --> 11:09.625
Oh, my mom.
Say hello.

11:09.958 --> 11:11.833
- Hello.
- Hello.

11:18.416 --> 11:20.875
Puppy, where is Bubbles?
It's time to sleep.

11:21.250 --> 11:23.208
Where is your snuggle pal?

11:23.291 --> 11:24.625
I can not find it.

11:25.166 --> 11:26.500
Where is Bubbles?

11:26.708 --> 11:28.625
-What?
-Bubbles. Where is it?

11:29.208 --> 11:30.750
I lost it in Alex's game.

11:31.125 --> 11:34.291
-What?
-You couldn't play if you didn't bet.

11:34.375 --> 11:36.208
He was very good
and he beat us all.

11:37.250 --> 11:38.333
Puppy.

11:38.625 --> 11:40.750
Bubbles is your snuggle pal.

11:41.125 --> 11:44.291
That is relative. It was mine,
but only because you gave it to me.

11:44.875 --> 11:47.791
Before it belonged to the company
that made it and now it belongs to Alex.

11:49.083 --> 11:50.083
Sorry?

11:50.208 --> 11:53.041
Attachment to things
only brings suffering, mom.

11:53.791 --> 11:55.750
Where did you get that, my love?

11:55.833 --> 11:57.666
From the podcast...

11:58.291 --> 11:59.875
"The death of the soul".

12:00.583 --> 12:02.541
By Pepe Mari Manzanares.

12:03.375 --> 12:05.208
Why are you talking like that, Puppy?

12:05.291 --> 12:07.916
Damn, mom.
Because the podcast is from Spain.

12:08.208 --> 12:09.791
You don't understand anything, gosh.

12:20.458 --> 12:22.875
He stole Bubbles
from our daughter.

12:22.958 --> 12:25.208
Moms have to be careful.
Always attentive.

12:25.291 --> 12:27.541
I'm not saying
Daniela is a bad mom.

12:27.625 --> 12:29.958
On the contrary,
I think she is a good mom.

12:30.041 --> 12:31.375
What do you think of her?

12:33.666 --> 12:35.708
Did you happen to talk
to her today?

12:36.583 --> 12:37.708
Aha.

12:39.416 --> 12:40.750
What did you talk about?

12:43.458 --> 12:46.041
I asked her
about that bitcoin thing,

12:46.125 --> 12:48.125
if now it was a good idea
to invest.

12:48.208 --> 12:50.083
Pig, no.
That's Julia, the blonde.

12:50.166 --> 12:53.208
I'm talking about the other one,
Daniela, very plain.

12:53.291 --> 12:55.708
The mother of the grant ginger,
the average woman.

12:57.333 --> 12:58.333
Aha.

12:59.333 --> 13:00.791
Did you talk to her then?

13:04.416 --> 13:06.625
Luna and the others say that...

13:07.583 --> 13:08.916
... that she is pretty.

13:09.666 --> 13:12.625
Maybe. Maybe she is attractive.
What do you think?

13:14.083 --> 13:15.791
Pig. What do you think?

13:16.666 --> 13:19.041
Does she seem pretty, attractive to you?

13:20.375 --> 13:21.833
Yes, she can be.

13:21.958 --> 13:23.958
Can be what?
Pretty or attractive?

13:25.250 --> 13:27.041
I do not know, my love.
She seems...

13:28.541 --> 13:29.625
... nice.

13:29.708 --> 13:32.541
Nice what?
Nice to look at or nice...

13:32.625 --> 13:34.625
-...psychologically speaking.
-Yes, that.

13:34.708 --> 13:37.041
What then?
Pick one option.

13:37.125 --> 13:39.458
Either one, my love.
I do not care.

13:39.541 --> 13:41.708
Let me finish answering this email.

13:49.791 --> 13:52.875
Mommies,
we have to address a high-impact topic.

13:53.166 --> 13:56.250
I'm talking about Alex
and his illegal gambling business.

13:56.458 --> 13:59.958
You know that yesterday
he took Bubbles from my poor Puppy.

14:00.041 --> 14:03.041
Bubbles is snuggle pal
for sweet dreams. Poor thing.

14:03.125 --> 14:05.083
He also kept a quartz from my Inti.

14:05.166 --> 14:07.791
And Juan de Dios' rosary
blessed by the Pope.

14:08.291 --> 14:12.041
He took $100 from James
and a GPS smartwatch from my son.

14:12.125 --> 14:15.500
But he did me a great favor,
with my Dante we are with STRT.

14:16.416 --> 14:18.875
-TTTT?
-Oh, what a pity!

14:18.958 --> 14:20.625
I hope you get better soon.

14:21.166 --> 14:23.458
It's not a disease, STRT.

14:23.625 --> 14:24.791
Kidney trauma?

14:24.875 --> 14:26.833
Screen time reduction therapy.

